			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well, the answer to the posts about charming a mage's pet is that the pet is qualified as a separate mob under the control (i.e. charmed) by the summoner until its death. However, if you break this charm by casting a charm of your own that has a less than &quot;'til death do ye part&quot; it will agro first on you for charming, the mage for summoning it, then become a freelance mob.<BR>
<BR>
New question: Can you charm two mobs, or have an animated Sword / Sheild pet as well as a charmed pet? I've seen it implied that it can be done in earlier posts, but never a &quot;Yes/No&quot; answer.<BR>
<BR>
Also, a good tatic is to charm those pesky griffawns in E. Karana. I was grouped with a level 15 (?) Enchanter once and he charmed a Griffawn and had it attack whatever he wanted. When charm wore off, he would recharm...I'm not sure exactly what went wrong, but I believe it had something to do with running out of mana...oh well. &lt;shrug&gt;
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
